Sentencas: This paper presents a hybrid metaheuristic optimizer called CHDJ to identify accurate and reliable values for the model parameters of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: CHDJ is a hybridizer of differential evolution (DE) and Jaya algorithm.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: The core of CHDJ lies in a developed competitive hybrid operation.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: In this operation, three vectors including the DE mutant vector, the Jaya mutant vector, and the crossover vector that constituted by the foregoing two mutant vectors form a tri-competitive mechanism together.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: This mechanism can contribute to exploring the global space extensively and exploiting the local region meticulously to generate promising candidate solutions.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: To verify the performance of CHDJ, two SOFC models including a cylindrical cell and a tubular stack operating at different pressures and temperatures are employed.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: Experimental results demonstrate that these three vectors interact and cooperate organically.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: They make CHDJ take full advantages of the exploration of DE and the exploitation of Jaya effectively.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: The optimal values of the mean square error (MSE) between the measured voltage and the calculated voltage obtained by CHDJ on the cylindrical cell at 1073K, 1173K, 1213K, and 1273K are 2.9215E-06, 1.4610E-06, 1.9093E-06, and 2.4682E-06, respectively.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: On the tubular stack, for the operating conditions of 3atm constant pressure at 873K, 923K, 973K, 1023K, and 1073K, the optimal MSE values are 2.7489E-05, 1.6169E-04, 6.9207E-04, 1.4833E-03, and 1.5876E-03, respectively.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: For the operating conditions of 1073K constant temperature under 1atm, 2atm, 3atm, 4atm, and 5atm, the results are 1.5293E-03, 1.6289E-03, 1.5876E-03, 1.5868E-03, and 1.5870E-03, respectively.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: Comparisons with other algorithms show that CHDJ achieves better overall performance.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm

Sentencas: It can skip local optima and find optimal solutions, and thus can serve as a hopeful candidate method for parameter identification of SOFC models.
Titulo: Optimal identification of solid oxide fuel cell parameters using a competitive hybrid differential evolution and Jaya algorithm
